<br>
Also, there was a great post about Angel of Night. It seems that AoN locks the targets First Aid. That can be a very good thing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/ukitkamran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KitKamran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 62<br> <font color=#660000>(6/13/02 1:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2018.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> not for PvM which is probably what the thread you read about in was from. But for mass-PVP attacks it's quite useful...your the MA in the group, everyone else concentrates on the doctors, you run into the massed group of soldiers/NTs/agents/traders/fixers and AoN their butts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , but you can do that with a low level AoN as good as any high level one.<br>
IMO the deflection shields suck major butt as it now stands and are nowhere near the IP required...the advanced versions might be worth it but the basic ones definently aren't.<br>
<br>
